{title: If Houses Had Hearts}
{artist: Wynn Stewart}
{composer: Written by Charlie Williams and Joe Nixon}

[G]If houses had hearts and [D7]feelings like people do
[C]Our house would cry its [D7]heart out for me and you
[G]Papers and milk bottles [C]left by the door
The [A7]lovers who lived there don't [D7]love anymore
And with [G]no one to care all the [C]flowers have died
If [Am]houses had [D7]feelings ([Am]houses had [D7]feelings) our house would [G]cry
If houses could hurt and [D7]remember like people do
[C]Our house would hurt [D7]remembering me and you
[G]Cobwebs in the corners and [C]dust on the floor
[A7]Laughter don't ring through its [D7]halls anymore
And the [G]fireplace is cold [C]where the flames have all died
If [Am]houses had [D7]feelings ([Am]houses had [D7]feelings) our house would [G]cry
There's [C]plenty of room for the [G]children to play
And [A7]shade trees will grow in the [D7]backyard someday
It's a [G]place to be happy if [C]two people try
If [Am]houses had [D7]feelings ([Am]houses had [D7]feelings) then our house would [G]cry